Tool Selection: I utilized Canva to design this visual guide,
leveraging its layout flexibility to house all five topics on a single, cohesive slide.

Design Contents: The infographic serves as a comprehensive roadmap for the modern student, covering:
-Digital Literacy: Defining it as the ability to find, evaluate, and communicate information across various digital platforms.
-Useful Digital Tools: Identifying essential software like Miro for collaboration and Notion for centralized note-taking.
-Safe Internet Practices: Highlighting "Cyber Hygiene," specifically focusing on password strength and recognizing phishing attempts.
-Professional Online Presence: Providing actionable tips for building a LinkedIn profile and managing a clean digital footprint.
-Email Etiquette: Outlining the necessity of professional subject lines, proper salutations, and concise messaging.

The Learning Process: One thing I found particularly challenging was the spatial management of all five topics. Fitting such a broad scope of information onto one slide required aggressive editing to ensure the design remained scannable and visually appealing.

Interesting Discovery: It was fascinating to see how email etiquette and online presence overlap; they aren't just separate skills, but a unified way of projecting credibility in a digital-first world.
